{
  "texts": [
    "As the evolution continues, a high-performance, heterogeneous vehicle computing platform takes the place of multiple DCUs for centralized computing.",
    "At the same time, all ZCUs are interconnected with the vehicle computing platform to collect and transmit information about ECUs around the vehicle.",
    "Ultimately, this high-performance platform establishes a connection with the cloud, culminating in an integrated control architecture spanning both the vehicle and the cloud.Hybrid E/E architectures, illustrated in Fig. 6, are deemed to exhibit more comprehensive performance compared to both domain-oriented and zone-oriented counterparts.",
    "This hybrid approach combines the merits of zone-oriented architectures by leveraging ZCUs to effectively minimize the number of ECUs.",
    "This leads to enhancements in wiring harness organization, scalability, and interchangeability."
  ]
}